The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Bengal | Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   BRIEFS
                  
	Durgapur, July 28: A 48-year-old man was beaten to death by armed dacoits on Sunday night after he spotted them scaling the wall of his neighbours house and raised an alarm. Police said Sasadhar Ghosh, a resident of Bishnupur in Bankura district, had gone out for a stroll near his house after dinner when he saw dacoits scaling the wall of Radhamadhab Goswamis house. The dacoits rushed to him, dragged him behind a bush and beat him to death.         
	Calcutta: Some 200 ticketless travellers were caught during a checking drive in Adra division of South Eastern Railway on Sunday. The special squad conducted surprise checks also in Bankura, Chhatna, Nobanda and Ondagram.         
	Calcutta: The state government would set up residential schools for child labourers in all 19 districts to rehabilitate them, minister of state Anadi Sahu told the Assembly.                                                                                                                                                                    
